Humans process visuals faster than text, making data visualization
a powerful tool for turning raw data into meaningful insights. Welldesigned visuals not only enhance understanding but also tell
compelling stories that drive action. Creating impactful
visualizations not only improves data interpretation but also
makes your portfolio stand out
Solution:-
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

categories = ['A', 'B', 'C']
values = [10, 24, 36]

plt.bar(categories, values, color='skyblue')
plt.title('Sample Bar Chart')
plt.xlabel('Category')
plt.ylabel('Value')
plt.show()
